de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.jrdf2vec.walk_generators.base

Enum WalkGenerationMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<WalkGenerationMode>
      • de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.jrdf2vec.walk_generators.base.WalkGenerationMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<WalkGenerationMode>

    public enum WalkGenerationMode
extends Enum<WalkGenerationMode>
    The available walk generation modes.

    Developer note:

    • There must be a runnable for each walk generation option.
    • The must be a resolution in evey implementation of IWalkGenerator.generateWalks(WalkGenerationMode, int, int, int, int, String) that shall support this walk mode. This affects, for example WalkGeneratorDefault.generateWalks(WalkGenerationMode, int, int, int, int, String) or WalkGeneratorDefault.generateWalks(WalkGenerationMode, int, int, int, int, String).

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      MID_WALKS
      Mid-walk walk generation: Given an entity, it is randomly decided whether to go backwards or forwards during the walk generation.
      MID_WALKS_DUPLICATE_FREE
      Mid-walk walk generation: Given an entity, it is randomly decided whether to go backwards or forwards during the walk generation.
      MID_WALKS_WEIGHTED
      Weighted mid-walk walk generation: Given an entity, it is randomly decided whether to go backwards or forwards randomly where the chances are determined by the number of options to go backwards and forwards: If there are more options to go backwards than forwards, the likelihood of going backwards is larger.
      RANDOM_WALKS
      Plain random walks generated in a forward-fashion (going backwards is not allowed).
      RANDOM_WALKS_DUPLICATE_FREE
      Plain random walks generated in a forward-fashion (going backwards is not allowed).

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • MID_WALKS

        public static final WalkGenerationMode MID_WALKS
        Mid-walk walk generation: Given an entity, it is randomly decided whether to go backwards or forwards during the walk generation.

      • MID_WALKS_DUPLICATE_FREE

        public static final WalkGenerationMode MID_WALKS_DUPLICATE_FREE
        Mid-walk walk generation: Given an entity, it is randomly decided whether to go backwards or forwards during the walk generation. The generated walks are free of duplicates. Due to the implementation this can lead to less generated walks than originally specified.

      • MID_WALKS_WEIGHTED

        public static final WalkGenerationMode MID_WALKS_WEIGHTED
        Weighted mid-walk walk generation: Given an entity, it is randomly decided whether to go backwards or forwards randomly where the chances are determined by the number of options to go backwards and forwards: If there are more options to go backwards than forwards, the likelihood of going backwards is larger. The generated walks are free of duplicates. Due to the implementation this can lead to less generated walks than originally specified.

      • RANDOM_WALKS

        public static final WalkGenerationMode RANDOM_WALKS
        Plain random walks generated in a forward-fashion (going backwards is not allowed).

      • RANDOM_WALKS_DUPLICATE_FREE

        public static final WalkGenerationMode RANDOM_WALKS_DUPLICATE_FREE
        Plain random walks generated in a forward-fashion (going backwards is not allowed). Duplicates are not allowed.
